                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300218-139-off770 t18300218-139-crimeloc774"></join>. On the 18th of February I came down from my own room over the stable, and went for some butter - I returned in about five minutes, and met the prisoner about fifteen yards from the stable door, with the box-coat on his shoulder; I asked where he was going with it - he said the servant sent him for it; I collared him, and took him back - it is my master's coat, but he said if I lost it I must make it good.</p>
